ZH: 航天员需要经过严格的训练才能进行太空任务。
EN: Astronauts need to undergo rigorous training to carry out space missions.

ZH: 航天员必须具备优秀的身体素质和心理素质。
EN: Astronauts must have excellent physical and mental qualities.

ZH: 航天员在太空中需要做很多的科学实验。
EN: Astronauts need to conduct a lot of scientific experiments in space.

ZH: 航天员要在极端环境中生存，因此他们需要具备耐心和勇气。
EN: Astronauts must survive in extreme environments, so they need to have patience and courage.

ZH: 航天员的工作需要团队合作和密切配合。
EN: The work of astronauts requires teamwork and close coordination.

ZH: 航天员的任务是探索未知的宇宙奥秘。
EN: The mission of astronauts is to explore the mysteries of the unknown universe.

ZH: 航天员需要戴着太空服才能在太空中工作。
EN: Astronauts need to wear space suits to work in space.

ZH: 航天员会面临很多挑战和风险。
EN: Astronauts will face many challenges and risks.

ZH: 航天员需要接受周期性的训练和评估。
EN: Astronauts need to undergo periodic training and evaluation.

ZH: 航天员的工作是为了推动人类的航天技术发展。
EN: The work of astronauts is to promote the development of human space technology.

ZH: 航天员需要在微重力环境中工作。
EN: Astronauts need to work in a microgravity environment.

ZH: 航天员需要乘坐宇宙飞船前往太空站。
EN: Astronauts need to ride spacecraft to go to space stations.

ZH: 航天员要学会处理太空中可能出现的紧急情况。
EN: Astronauts need to learn how to handle emergencies that may occur in space.

ZH: 航天员的工作需要高度的自律和自我管理能力。
EN: The work of astronauts requires high levels of self-discipline and self-management skills.

ZH: 航天员需要经历严格的选拔程序才能成为一名宇航员。
EN: Astronauts need to go through a rigorous selection process to become a spaceman.

ZH: 航天员必须具备扎实的科学和技术背景。
EN: Astronauts must have a solid background in science and technology.

ZH: 航天员的工作多数时间都在太空站中度过。
EN: Astronauts spend most of their time in space stations.

ZH: 航天员的工作需要耐心和细心。
EN: The work of astronauts requires patience and attention to detail.

ZH: 航天员需要适应长时间在太空中的生活。
EN: Astronauts need to adapt to living in space for long periods of time.

ZH: 航天员是人类探索宇宙的勇士。
EN: Astronauts are the warriors of human exploration in the universe.
